How long are you going to keep Takagi waiting?
Just tell him to go on ahead.
You have got no time to eat breakfast, right?
It is okay, I will buy something on the way.
You need to eat something before leaving.
Yeah, especially after starting our serialization.
Hey, what are you going to do about college?
Well I did make that promise with my parents, so I need keep that in mind.
If TRAP becomes a really popular manga, I may not go...
Our seventh chapter was 13th in the rankings, though...
There is no sense in rushing it.
We are going to continue with our current style.
But you still have some left.
Saiko, you have lost some weight since we started the serialization.
Yeah, my pants are pretty loose now.
But every minute spent eating is a minute wasted.
I am in the same class as Mashiro!
I could not be in the same class as you...
Even if we are in different classes, we see each other every day anyways.
It is up one rank from the early results!
And last week's case-concluding chapter got 10th, too.
The new serializations start next week.
You have done nothing but sigh lately.
Speaking of which, you have not said a word about TRAP.
Are not you worried about them?
It is okay to continue to push it as a mystery, right?
I would feel more at ease if they had a better ranking.
I do not want them to be overlooked just because they have less experience.
If experience led to popularity, the rankings would be ordered by the authors' ages.
Um, but is not good sense something you are born with?
In other words, there is only a paper-thin difference between a romanticist and a humanist.
What is with the humanist thing, anyway?
I could forgive you as a human, but as an otter, I cannot!
Otters is pretty wordy, but it is really popular.
I wonder what is so different?
We also think that both Otters and TRAP are different from normal Jack fare.
Is it better to have more jokes, after all?
If so, then you just have to put jokes into TRAP.
But TRAP is not a gag manga.
Otters is a story manga too, though.
Well, comparing manga in the same genre can be difficult.
I think you should stick to the mystery conventions for TRAP.
But you could make it a bit more lighthearted.
Oh yeah, Miura said something similar.
You need the sense for it.
Are you saying I do not have a sense for jokes?
Hmm... your face is pretty funny.
I am going to go out and buy as much comedy software as I can.
I have already thought about criminal psychology, so now I will study humor.
If I do that, maybe I can figure out how to add in some lightheartedness.
He says some pretty stupid stuff sometimes, but I really like how he works so hard!
I wanted to calculate the right amount of lightheartedness and fun to put in...
I also went around to as many bookstores as I could and bought all the books that had Famous Lines in the title!
I was thinking of studying other genres after comedy, too!
But what gave you the same idea?
I thought of it after looking at Otters 11 .
The manga's art is bad, but it is got good dialogue sense.
It is kind of pointless, but somehow, it is funny.
Takagi, you quickly put what you learn to good use.
If you do that now, we will definitely rise in the rankings.
Let us make your next story with that in mind.
All right, let us have our meeting.
You cannot just plagiarize them, though.
You have to study them hard and make your own style.
Those two are getting so serious just to raise the ranking slightly...
I have to improve my art, too!
Then let us start with this page.
KIYOSHI Knights took the top ranking in the early results!
If this keeps up, the next team leader will be...
Do not get cocky just because KIYOSHI got the top spot.
Come on, it is not like that at all.
Your face does not match your words.
Why is not Miura telling us the ranking of the eighth chapter?
I can only assume it must be a ranking that is hard to say.
And I am afraid to ask him myself.
If this keeps up, we will really need to rely on the dialogue from chapter 11 onwards...
We cannot use it as-is, but...
I will use it as a reference.
I have kind of figured out the basic rules.
I hope the rankings of chapter 11 onwards will go up with this.
So... our ranking for chapter eight was that bad, huh?
Since it still is not official, I did not want to tell you and have you celebrating too early.
Ah, KIYOSHI fell to 2nd place in the official ranking.
But it lost the 1 ranking by a margin of 6.
That is passable, is not it?
The official ranking is still 9th place!
Even though new manga started their serializations!
If their ranking went up even a bit, should not you be happy?
But why did it go up?
Oh, hideout door placed 1st in the official ranking!
Well, the first chapter is especially well made.
The ninth chapter of TRAP got 8th place!
Well then, I will announce the official ranking of the 10th chapter.
So I guess that means for the next story, there was no need to polish the dialogue.
We have to aim even higher!
We were right to trust in Shujin's stories after all!
How dare your 10th chapter surpass my 3rd chapter!
Our second chapter is 5th in the survey!
I am getting really pumped up somehow!
Sensei, you are bothering the neighbors!
Well, he said he was going on a trip or something...
Ashirogi's ranking went up, as I thought.
I think Ashirogi will become my rival.
They had the same eyes as a super energetic manga protagonist.
Fukuda, Nakai, and Aoki were all serialized, and they are all trying hard.
Drawing for Jack just got a lot more fun.
We have not started revising the script.
It is because the case was resolved well!
It is getting established as a genuine mystery!
I could not give these to you without checking the contents first, so it is taken some time but...
Yes, they are all fan letters addressed to Ashirogi Mutou.
You will notice if you check the postmarks, but there are many more recent ones than from the beginning of your serialization.
This may support what Mashiro said about TRAP being established as a mystery.
But now it feels like I am under a different kind of pressure...
Maybe we will make a huge jump in the rankings with this!
The way he brilliantly solves the mysteries is really cool.
On top of that, there is definitely much more wit in the dialogue.
Mr. Takagi, since chapter 14 seems fine, please look over the summary of the short novels I read this week.
I worked hard and read five!
Hey, can I take a look at your fan letters?
Should not we be paying Miyoshi as an assistant, or something?
She is doing it because she wants to.
What are you two whispering about over there?
Oh, we are just talking about how you are such a great girl.
Right, right... and we were thinking of expressing our thanks for your help every day.
All right, we have expressed our thanks, so let us revise the storyboard!
I will think of something even better for our next series.
And I will support you even more!
Shujin and Miyoshi are giving it all they have got.
I should find a way to do that with my art.
Wow, Mashiro's art is really something.
You have not been sleeping in school lately, so when do you sleep?
From about 5 AM until the last minute, at 8 AM.
Actually, we may be in trouble with chapter 14.
No, I am behind schedule because of stuff like the composition being too stiff.
I can make it if I stay up all night.
I will not let it because problems for everyone.
Do not push yourself too hard.
We actually have until Monday to turn it in.
Chapter 11 is coming in at 7th place in the early rankings!
This means it was not a fluke that chapter 10 got 6th place!
Will you rewrite the storyboard for chapter six?
I think the main outline is good,
but there should be some more action.
The panels need to be flashier.
But Aida said it was fine.
Will you trust me more than him?
Expand on the action scenes and split the chapter into two parts.
Also, the readers might get tired of the dense dialogue.
Please be aware that this is a shounen manga.
Our 11th place ranking for chapter three is not that great.
Do it for us, for hideout door!
I will try doing what you suggested.
I trust you when it comes to manga, at least.
She also mentioned that she went to a post-recording session of the anime version of Jack's SKET DANCE.
Just as a guest role, it seems.
They have gotten ahead of us.
I wanted Miho to make her Jack debut in an anime version of TRAP.
But it is proof that Azuki's been working hard.
So it is only right that I should congratulate her.
She did work hard for this.
It seems like all of us have luck on our side.
We will aim higher as well!
I thought so, since you were not back when I woke up.
I have not penned this in!
I still have three pages that are only rough sketches!
And the assistants will be here at 4!
Sorry, Mom, but please call the school and tell them I will be absent!
Go to school like you are supposed to!
I have not skipped school even once since becoming a senior,
Hey, Mashiro did not come to school today...
He said he fell asleep after we left.
He is penning-in pages right now.
Well, something like this happened during our serialization practice run with Hattori.
I am sorry for missing the deadline.
With this level of quality, there will be times when you are late by a day or two.
Maybe your ranking will rise even more!
I will definitely give you the next one on Friday.
That manner of speech... could you possibly be...
I do not know that guy.
Um, could you possibly be Takemitsu Shinzou?
We are also heading towards an anime adaptation, bit by bit!
Your 14th chapter and CROW are tied for 3rd place!
Tied with CROW... with Niizuma Eiji?
An anime adaption is not just a dream.
Even though KIYOSHI got 6th place, I cannot celebrate!
6th place is still great, you know.
It seems your decision to change things was the correct one.
Show it to me before Aida from now on.
Looks like I have become less popular.
How about I take a break for now...
I will not let you say that 9th place is not popular.
Though it is probably good news for you.
I do not want to lose to Ashirogi.
Honestly, I never thought we would tie with CROW.
Oh yeah, Hattori did tell the lead editor that we would overtake Niizuma in three years.
It is been just about three years since that workshop.
We can make his words a reality.
No, surpassing him will be our thanks to Hattori!
I got us a front page color spread for the 20th chapter!
Your first volume goes on sale that day.
That shows just how much is expected from it.
The first edition of volume one is getting 100,000 prints, after all.
It is rare for the first volume of a newly serialized manga to get that many prints!
The first volume of Otters 11 is being released on the same day, and it is only getting 60,000.
We have got more than Otters?
Well, 150,000 volumes of CROW were printed recently, though.
But the way things are going, TRAP will need a second printing soon.
No, while we are at it, let us aim for a million prints!
A million prints would normally happen after it gets an anime.
If it is made into an anime, it will be more well known, right?
I want to try applying screentone, too!
Thank you, but it is instant.
Just the fact that a girl prepared it puts me at ease.
Anyway, you guys are really something!
It must be hell, going through high school while keeping up with a serialization.
Well, we are splitting the art and the story.
Niizuma is inhuman for being able to do both.
But all he did was give me medicine and send me away.
If you were hospitalized, you would not be able to draw your manuscript, right?
Mashiro, can I talk to you for a minute?
If you lose popularity, that is it for you!
This is my dream job, though.
It is a nightmare for me!
Hiramaru seems like the type who would vent his stress like that.
This is Yoshida from Shounen Jack.
They have come to pick me up.
He seems rather used to it.
Well then, we will get going.
We are counting on you tomorrow, too.
Mashiro, you have been redrawing your art for the past few chapters, have not you?
We have assisted you with various parts, but this rate of progress is stunning.
I am also happy to be working on TRAP!
The official ranking of chapter 15 was 6th place.
He is got another lead on you.
But we will turn it around with chapter 20's front page color spread!
I did a sketch of the volume's cover!
It will look even better once you color it in!
No one can compare with Mashiro's one-page shots!
Yasu, it is all thanks to you.
Then give me a 2,000 yen raise for each good idea!
Actually, I was getting help from my friends and paying them 500 yen per idea!
But I really want 1,000 yen for myself!
You... you subcontracted my profit margin?!
I will give you a raise of 3,000 yen!
Ooh, that is Godly Fukuda for you!
What is with that rough sketch?!
It is time to get serious and do this work.
The next time you turn in a manuscript, I will take you out to a place with cute girls.
Mr. Yoshida, I will give it my all.
I will try my best this time.
That will work for two weeks.
I should make it at this pace.
Oh, now I have done it.
Takahama, do you always get here this early?
Since we are headed the same way, you do not mind if I walk with you, do you?
He seems really shy and cute.
I think it is the girl who had a part in SKET DANCE.
He is probably in the bathroom, or something.
It looks like he fell asleep.
There is good jokes and bad jokes
But it is weird that he did not wake up when you screamed.
It was just impossible to keep up while still in school!
But that is his dream, and our dream.
Can you stop a dream that is already been set in motion?
